Enter y-coordinate of the point: 2
Enter radius of the circle: 1
Distance from origin = 2.8284271247461903
The point is outside the circleEnter x-coordinate of the point: 0
Enter y-coordinate of the point: 0
Enter radius of the circle: 0
Distance from origin = 0.0
The point lies on the circle

'''
1) What  are  the  outputs  if  input  is  -6 ? --->
2) What  are  the  outputs  if  input  is  15  ?  --->
3) What  are  the  outputs  if  input  is  10.8  ?  --->
4) What  are  the  outputs  if  input  is  0  ?  --->
5) What  are  the  outputs  if  input  is  -10  ?  --->
6) What  are  the  outputs  if  input  is  7  ?  --->
'''
x = eval(input('Enter any  number :  '))
match  x:
	case  7 |  -6  |  0:
		print('Hyd')
		print('Sec')
		print('Cyb')
	case  -10 | 15:
		print('One')
		print('Two')
		print('Three')
	case  _:
		print('India')
		print('China')
		print('Usa')
# End  of  match
print('Bye')

